article_title: New Partnerships To Aid Walgreen's Growth But Higher Promotional Investment Can Impact Margins

article_metadata.description: By 2016, Walgreen aims to achieve the following four goals: 1) sales of $130 billion including Alliance Boots share, associates and joint venture sales; 2) synergies of $1 billion; 3) operating cash flow of $8 billion and 4) net debt of $11 billion. As per its performance to-date, the company claims to be slightly ahead of its expectations.
article_metadata.author: Great Speculations
